--- a/supabase/functions/taskweft-edge/AtomVM.mjs  (generated by mix popcorn.cook --include-vm)
+++ b/supabase/functions/taskweft-edge/AtomVM.mjs  (patched for Deno / Supabase Edge Runtime)
@@ Hunk 1 — minimum_runtime_check.js: skip Node.js detection @@
-  var currentNodeVersion = typeof process !== "undefined" && process.versions?.node ? humanReadableVersionToPacked(process.versions.node) : TARGET_NOT_SUPPORTED;
+  var currentNodeVersion = TARGET_NOT_SUPPORTED; // patched for Deno/non-browser

Reason: Deno exposes `process.versions.node` for Node.js compatibility.
Emscripten's runtime check throws if it detects Node.js because AtomVM.mjs
was compiled with -sENVIRONMENT=web,worker (not node). Forcing
currentNodeVersion = TARGET_NOT_SUPPORTED bypasses the throw.

@@ Hunk 2 — ENVIRONMENT detection: force ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE = false @@
-var ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE = globalThis.process?.versions?.node && globalThis.process?.type != "renderer";
+var ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE = false; // patched for Deno

Reason: Same root cause. Deno's process compat makes this true, but the
downstream assert `assert(!ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE, ...)` would then fail.
ENVIRONMENT_IS_WEB stays true (Deno exposes globalThis.window), so
AtomVM correctly runs as a web environment.

@@ Hunk 3 — disable the ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE assert @@
-assert(!ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE, "node environment detected but not enabled at build time (add `node` to `-sENVIRONMENT` to enable)");
+// patched: assert(!ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE, "node environment detected but not enabled at build time (add `node` to `-sENVIRONMENT` to enable)");

Reason: Belt-and-suspenders; with Hunk 2 applied ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE is
already false, so this assert would pass anyway. Commented out to make the
intent explicit.

--- How to re-apply after `mix popcorn.cook --include-vm` regenerates AtomVM.mjs ---

Run from the repo root:
  bash scripts/patch_atomvm_deno.sh

Or manually (search strings are stable across Popcorn 0.2.x builds):

  sed -i '' \
    's/var currentNodeVersion = typeof process !== "undefined" && process\.versions?\.node ? humanReadableVersionToPacked(process\.versions\.node) : TARGET_NOT_SUPPORTED;/var currentNodeVersion = TARGET_NOT_SUPPORTED; \/\/ patched for Deno\/non-browser/' \
    supabase/functions/taskweft-edge/AtomVM.mjs

  sed -i '' \
    's/var ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE = globalThis\.process?\.versions?\.node && globalThis\.process?\.type != "renderer";/var ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE = false; \/\/ patched for Deno/' \
    supabase/functions/taskweft-edge/AtomVM.mjs

  sed -i '' \
    's/assert(!ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE, "node environment detected but not enabled at build time/\/\/ patched: assert(!ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE, "node environment detected but not enabled at build time/' \
    supabase/functions/taskweft-edge/AtomVM.mjs
